Russia’s RTS Stock-Index Futures Advance at Start of Trading

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-03-11T16:39:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/russia-s-rts-stock-index-futures-advance-at-start-of-trading.html
  Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
gained at the start of trading.  Futures on the dollar-denominated index expiring in March
added 0.1 percent to 192,195 at 11:21 a.m. in  New York .  Contracts on OAO Sberbank, Russia’s largest lender, and
futures on OAO Gazprom, the natural-gas export monopoly, were
little changed. Contracts on OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-
biggest oil producer, rose 0.4 percent. The Market Vectors
Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that holds Russian shares, fell
0.5 percent, declining for a sixth consecutive day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
